sg.danielneutrinos.jmdictlib.data

Class KanjiElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • sg.danielneutrinos.jmdictlib.data.KanjiElement

  • public class KanjiElement
extends java.lang.Object
    The defining component of each entry. The overwhelming majority of entries will have a single kanji element associated with a word in Japanese. Where there are multiple kanji elements within an entry, they will be orthographical variants of the same word, either using variations in okurigana, or alternative and equivalent kanji. Common "mis-spellings" may be included, provided they are associated with appropriate information fields. Synonyms are not included; they may be indicated in the cross-reference field associated with the sense element.

    • Field Detail

      • kanji

        private java.lang.String kanji
        A word or short phrase in Japanese which is written using at least one non-kana character (usually kanji, but can be other characters). The valid characters are kanji, kana, related characters such as chouon and kurikaeshi, and in exceptional cases, letters from other alphabets.

      • primaries

        private java.util.List<java.lang.String> primaries
        Information about the relative priority of the entry, and consist of codes indicating the word appears in various references which can be taken as an indication of the frequency with which the word is used. This field is intended for use either by applications which want to concentrate on entries of a particular priority, or to generate subset files.

      • info

        private java.util.List<java.lang.String> info
        Information field related specifically to the orthography of the keb, and will typically indicate some unusual aspect, such as okurigana irregularity.
